---
/**
 * Pre-Marital Counselling Page
 * ============================
 * Services page for pre-marital counselling.
 */

import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Pre-Marital Counselling Services"
  description="Building Strong Foundations for a Happy and Lasting Marriage with experienced family law consultants and relationship counsellors."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Services</span>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Pre-Marital Counselling</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="page-title">Pre-Marital Counselling Services</h1>
      <p class="page-update">
        Building Strong Foundations for a Happy and Lasting Marriage
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="legal-content section-padding">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <article class="legal-article">
          <p class="intro">
            Marriage is one of the most important decisions in life. However, in
            recent years, a significant number of marriages face serious
            challenges soon after the wedding, and many couples unfortunately
            find themselves involved in matrimonial disputes and divorce
            proceedings within the first few years of marriage.
            <br /><br />
            With over 22 years of experience in Family Court litigation and matrimonial
            matters, we have witnessed the common issues that often lead to marital
            discord, emotional distress, and legal disputes. Many of these problems
            can be identified, discussed, and addressed before marriage through proper
            guidance and professional counselling.
            <br /><br />
            To help couples build stronger, healthier, and more informed relationships,
            we offer Pre-Marital Counselling Services in association with experienced
            professional counsellors.
          </p>

          <h2>Why Pre-Marital Counselling?</h2>
          <p>
            Pre-marital counselling provides an opportunity for couples to
            understand each other better before entering into marriage. It helps
            identify expectations, values, compatibility factors, communication
            styles, and potential areas of conflict that may arise in married
            life.
          </p>
          <p>Our counselling sessions are designed to assist couples in:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Understanding each other's personalities and behavioural patterns.
            </li>
            <li>Discussing expectations from marriage.</li>
            <li>Improving communication and conflict-resolution skills.</li>
            <li>Understanding financial planning and responsibilities.</li>
            <li>Discussing career aspirations and work-life balance.</li>
            <li>Understanding family values and relationships with in-laws.</li>
            <li>
              Discussing children, parenting philosophies, and future planning.
            </li>
            <li>Understanding emotional and psychological compatibility.</li>
            <li>
              Identifying potential areas of disagreement and learning healthy
              ways to address them.
            </li>
            <li>Building trust, respect, and mutual understanding.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Who Should Attend?</h2>
          <p>Our Pre-Marital Counselling Program is suitable for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Engaged couples planning to marry soon.</li>
            <li>
              Couples whose marriage has been arranged and who wish to
              understand each other better.
            </li>
            <li>Couples in a committed relationship considering marriage.</li>
            <li>
              Families who wish to ensure that the prospective bride and groom
              enter marriage with realistic expectations and a strong
              foundation.
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Our Approach</h2>
          <p>Our counselling process combines:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Practical insights gained from handling matrimonial and family
              disputes for over 22 years.
            </li>
            <li>
              Professional counselling techniques by experienced relationship
              counsellors.
            </li>
            <li>Confidential and unbiased discussions.</li>
            <li>Structured sessions tailored to the needs of each couple.</li>
            <li>
              Guidance focused on prevention rather than conflict resolution
              after problems arise.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The objective is not to judge compatibility or influence personal
            decisions, but to help couples make informed choices and prepare
            themselves for a successful and fulfilling married life.
          </p>

          <h2>Benefits of Pre-Marital Counselling</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Better understanding between partners.</li>
            <li>Improved communication and emotional connection.</li>
            <li>Reduced risk of misunderstandings and future conflicts.</li>
            <li>Increased awareness of responsibilities and expectations.</li>
            <li>Stronger emotional preparedness for married life.</li>
            <li>Enhanced ability to manage challenges together as a team.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
          <p>
            All discussions and counselling sessions are conducted with the
            utmost confidentiality, professionalism, and respect for the privacy
            of both individuals.
          </p>

          <h2>Invest in Your Relationship Before Marriage</h2>
          <p>
            A successful marriage is built not merely on love and attraction,
            but on understanding, communication, trust, and mutual respect.
          </p>
          <p>
            Pre-marital counselling is a proactive step towards creating a
            stronger relationship and reducing the possibility of future marital
            conflicts.
          </p>
          <blockquote>
            "Know Your Partner Before Marriage – Build a Foundation for a
            Lifetime."
          </blockquote>

          <h2>Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            For appointments, counselling sessions, and further information,
            please contact:
          </p>

          <div class="contact-box">
            <p>
              <strong>Advocate Pradnya Pednekar</strong><br />
              Advocate & Family Law Consultant<br />
              22+ Years of Experience in Matrimonial and Family Court Matters<br
              /><br />
              <strong>Phone:</strong> +91-9152109228<br />
              <strong>Email:</strong> applegalservices26@gmail.com<br />
              <strong>Office Address:</strong> B-19, 2nd Floor, Shanti Bhavan, Arihant
              Shopping Center, J.S.D. Road, Next to Mulund Railway Station, Mulund(W),
              Mumbai - 400080 , Maharashtra, India<br /><br />
              <em>By Appointment Only.</em>
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: linear-gradient(
      135deg,
      var(--color-primary-900) 0%,
      var(--color-primary-700) 100%
    );
    color: white;
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  }
  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-500);
  }
  .breadcrumb span {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  }
  .breadcrumb span:last-child {
    color: var(--color-accent-500);
  }

  .page-title {
    color: white;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .page-update {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  }

  .legal-content {
    background: var(--surface-primary);
  }

  .content-wrapper {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--text-body);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .legal-article h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-light);
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  /* Global dark mode override for headings */
  :global([data-theme="dark"]) .legal-article h2 {
    color: var(--text-heading);
  }

  .legal-article p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-article ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-article li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  blockquote {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-accent-600);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-500);
    margin: 2rem 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--surface-secondary);
    border-radius: 0 0.5rem 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .contact-box {
    background: var(--surface-body);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-500);
  }

  .contact-box p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-body);
  }
</style>
